# Tribunal cron entry for VM (OpenClaw)
#
# VM gu-log path: /home/clawd/clawd/projects/gu-log/
# Runs the 4-stage all-Claude tribunal on backlog articles.
#
# Environment requirements:
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY  — Claude OAuth token for `claude` CLI
#   GU_LOG_DIR         — path to gu-log repo (set below)
#   TZ                 — Asia/Taipei for correct quiet-hours logic
#
# Quiet hours are enforced inside tribunal-all-claude.sh itself
# (weekday 20:00-02:00 TST — script will sleep and resume automatically).
#
# How to install on VM:
#   crontab -e    # add lines below
#
# Run tribunal on the oldest unprocessed article every 6 hours:
# 0 */6 * * * TZ=Asia/Taipei GU_LOG_DIR=/home/clawd/clawd/projects/gu-log /home/clawd/clawd/projects/gu-log/scripts/tribunal-cron-runner.sh >> /home/clawd/logs/tribunal.log 2>&1

# ─── Alternatively: run tribunal-all-claude.sh directly on a specific file ───
# 30 9 * * 1-5 TZ=Asia/Taipei GU_LOG_DIR=/home/clawd/clawd/projects/gu-log bash /home/clawd/clawd/projects/gu-log/scripts/tribunal-all-claude.sh <filename.mdx> >> /home/clawd/logs/tribunal.log 2>&1

# ─── SP pipeline invocation (Go binary, canonical as of Phase 4) ──────────
# 0 10 * * 1-5 TZ=Asia/Taipei GU_LOG_DIR=/home/clawd/clawd/projects/gu-log /home/clawd/clawd/projects/gu-log/tools/sp-pipeline/sp-pipeline run --opus <tweet_url> >> /home/clawd/logs/sp-pipeline.log 2>&1

# ─── Backwards-compat shim (still works — execs into the Go binary above) ─
# 0 10 * * 1-5 TZ=Asia/Taipei GU_LOG_DIR=/home/clawd/clawd/projects/gu-log bash /home/clawd/clawd/projects/gu-log/scripts/sp-pipeline.sh --opus <tweet_url> >> /home/clawd/logs/sp-pipeline.log 2>&1
